Subject: [PATCH] opcache: honor opcache.dups_fix in the function-table copy too

opcache.dups_fix makes opcache keep the first definition and skip the
duplicate instead of fataling with "Cannot redeclare". The class-table
copy (_zend_accel_class_hash_copy) already honors it; the function-table
copy (_zend_accel_function_hash_copy) does not — it goes straight to the
"Cannot redeclare function" fatal regardless of the directive.

This makes the function copy consistent with the class copy: when
opcache.dups_fix is enabled, a duplicate function definition is skipped
(first-wins) rather than fatal.

Motivation: long-running application servers (e.g. ZealPHP) that
re-execute require_once'd files per request can hit opcache's
load_script re-copy with the symbol already installed; dups_fix already
covers the class case but the function case still fatals.

--- a/ext/opcache/zend_accelerator_util_funcs.c
+++ b/ext/opcache/zend_accelerator_util_funcs.c
@@ -159,7 +159,13 @@ static zend_always_inline void _zend_accel_function_hash_copy(HashTable *target,
 		ZEND_ASSERT(p->key);
 		t = zend_hash_find_known_hash(target, p->key);
 		if (UNEXPECTED(t != NULL)) {
-			goto failure;
+			/* Honor opcache.dups_fix for functions too — the class-table
+			 * copy above already does. Keep the first-declared function and
+			 * skip the duplicate instead of fataling. */
+			if (!ZCG(accel_directives).ignore_dups) {
+				goto failure;
+			}
+			continue;
 		}
 		_zend_hash_append_ptr_ex(target, p->key, Z_PTR(p->val), 1);
 		if (UNEXPECTED(call_observers) && *ZSTR_VAL(p->key)) { // if not rtd key
